HEADWORD: Histozyme
<hw>His"to*zyme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ tissue +
<?/ leaven.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A soluble enzyme
occurring in the animal body, to the presence of which many normal
decompositions and synthetical processes are supposed to be
due.</def>⟦br⟧
